                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.5045/64: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-06-04T12:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 4, 1925—noon</hi>.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 4—5:57 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>201. Following from consul, Changsha: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“June 3, 1 p.m. Students of all the schools in Changsha striking today
                            because of the May 30th affray in Shanghai. Many private rikishas
                            demolished last evening on the main streets. Boycott against British and
                            Japanese declared. The situation is serious but is under control.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Mayer</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
